ms2 Overview
=========================
ms2 is a molecular simulation software developed to calculate thermodynamic equilibrium properties of homogenous pure fluids or mixtures. This software is designed to provide a user-friendly molecular modeling and simulation package for both academic institutions and the chemical industry. 

Quickstart quide
=========================
Requirements: 	
- FORTRAN compiler, e.g. GNU Fortran or Intel oneAPI
- for parallel execution: Open MPI or openMP
				
Compile the source code: 	
- change into the directory "src" containing all source code files

Execute either of the following commands for compiling: 
- with Intel ifx: make COMPILER=INTEL
- with Intel ifx using MPI: make COMPILER=INTEL MPI=1
- with GNU Fortran: make COMPILER=GNU
- with GNU Fortran using MPI: make COMPILER=GNU MPI=1

to create the respective executables:		
- with Intel ifx: ms2_INTEL
- with Intel ifx using MPI: ms2_INTEL_mpi
- with GNU Fortran: ms2_GNU
- with GNU Fortran using MPI: ms2_GNU_mpi

	
Execution instructions
=========================		
To run the program, use the following command format:
/path/to/executable [options] input_file.par
- input_file.par: input file containing general simulation parameters, ensemble specific boundary conditions and specification of state point
- input_file.pm: specified in input_file.par, contains force field model of molecular species
- [options]: -r restart simulation from the state saved in *.rst 

Documentation
=========================	
A detailed documentation can be found at https://github.com/moltherm-computation/ms2_documentation.		

Directory structure
=========================
ms2/
- src/     					# source code files
- ms2.F90 				# main routine
- ms2_accumulator.F90    # contains TAccumulator object for ensemble averages
- ms2_component.F90 		# data and functions dealing with all molecules of a given molecular type	
- ms2_ensemble.F90 		# ensemble is set up and initialized.
- ms2_global.F90 		# declarations of global constants and functions 
- ms2_interaction.F90 	# determines interaction partners
- ms2_molecule.F90 		# data regarding the basic structure of a molecule
- ms2_potential.F90 		# force and potential energy calculations according to intermolecular potential
- ms2_simulation.F90		# setup and control of the simulation    
- ms2_site.F90  			# position of a site with respect to the center of mass of a molecule
- ms2_stopwatch.F90		# measures execution time of program segments
- ms2_version.F90    	# declarations of version string and variable 
- Makefile		    	# taget build rules, module dependencies
- makefiles/	    		# contains compiler-related makefiles



	

 							
 							
 							
 							
 							
